claims:
Claims 1. A method, comprising: detecting creation or modification of a content item; determining a content item namespace to which the content item belongs; selecting a target content item block server to which the content item namespace is assigned; identifying one or more content item blocks of the content item that are not stored at the target content item block server; and uploading, to the target content item block server, the one or more content item blocks of the content item that were not stored at the target content item block server. 2. The method of Claim 1, wherein the detecting creation or modification of the content item is based, at least in part, on detecting when a file corresponding to the content item is created or modified in a file system, remote from the target content item block server, at which the content item namespace is mounted. 3. The method of Claim 1, wherein the determining the content item namespace to which the content item belongs is based, at least in part, on: a) a file system path to a file corresponding to the content item, and b) a file system path to a mount point of the content item namespace in a file system local to a computing system storing the one or more content items blocks. 4. The method of Claim 1, wherein the selecting the target content item block server to which the content item namespace is assigned is based, at least in part, on determining that an identifier of the content item namespace is associated with an identifier of the target content item block server in data representing assignments of content item namespaces to content item block servers. 5. The method of Claim 1, wherein the selecting the target content item block server to which the content item namespace is assigned is based, at least in part, on determining that an identifier of the content item namespace is associated with an identifier of the target content item block server in data representing assignments of content item namespaces to content item block servers; and wherein the method further comprises obtaining the data representing the assignments from a metadata server other than the target content item block server. 6. The method of Claim 1, further comprising: determining a current client journal cursor value based, at least in part, on the content item namespace; sending the current client journal cursor value to a metadata server; and receiving, from the metadata server, one or more identifiers of the one or more content item blocks of the content item that are not stored at the target block server. 7. The method of Claim 1, further compri obtaining a first set of identifiers of content item blocks of the created or modified content item; sending the first set of identifiers to a metadata server; and receiving a second set of one or more identifiers from the metadata server, the second set of one or more identifiers identifying the one or more content item blocks that are not stored at the target content item block server. 8. The method of Claim 1, wherein: the content item is a first content item; the target content item block server is a first target content item block server; and the method further comprises: detecting creation or modification of a second content item that is not the first content item; determining that the second content item belongs to the content item namespace; selecting a second target content item block server, that is not the first target content item block server, based, at least in part, on the content item namespace; and uploading, to the second target content item block server, one or more content item blocks of the second content item. 9. The method of Claim 1, wherein: the content item is a first content item; the content item namespace is a first content item namespace; and the method further comprises: detecting creation or modification of a second content item that is not the first content item; determining that the second content item belongs to a second content item namespace that is not the first content item namespace; identifying that the second content item namespace is assigned to the target content item block server; and uploading, to the target content item block server, one or more content item blocks of the second content item that. The method of Claim 1, further comprising: sending a current client journal cursor value to a metadata server, the current client journal cursor value associated with the content item namespace and content item block server to which the content item namespace is assigned; 

 based, at least in part, on the sending the current client journal cursor value, receiving, from the metadata server, a first set of identifiers of content item blocks corresponding to at least one block that makes up the content item, wherein the content item belongs to the content item namespace; based, at least in part, on the receiving the first set of content item block identifiers, determining one or more content item blocks of the content item that are not locally stored by the computing system; and downloading, to the computing system from a second content item block server, the one or more content item blocks of the content item that were not locally stored by the computing system. 11. The method of Claim 1, further comprising: receiving, from a client, (A) an identifier of the content item namespace and (B) a first set of identifiers of first content item blocks, the first content item blocks making up a first version of the content item stored at the client, the content item belonging to the content item namespace; selecting a content item block server to which the content item namespace is assigned; based, at least in part, on the first set of identifiers, determining a second set of identifiers of second content item blocks, the second content item blocks making up a second version of the content item stored at the content item block server; and sending, to the client, one or more content item block identifiers that are in the first set that are not in the second set. 12. The method of Claim 1, further comprising: detecting a new content item belonging to the content item namespace; determining a client at which the content item namespace is mounted; notifying the client that an update to the content item namespace is available; receiving, from the client, a current client journal cursor value, the current client journal cursor value associated with the content item namespace and a content item block server to which the content item namespace is assigned; based, at least in part, on the received current client journal cursor value, obtaining a set of identifiers of content item blocks, of which the new content item is composed, stored at the content item block server; and sending the set of content item block identifiers to the client. 13. A method performed by a computing system, the method comprising: sending a current client journal cursor value to a metadata server, the current client journal cursor value associated with a content item namespace and a first content item block server to which the content item namespace is assigned; 

