locks, the second content item blocks making up a second version of the content item stored at the content item block server; and sending, to the client, one or more content item block identifiers that are in the first set that are not in the second set. 18. The method of Claim 17, further comprising: receiving an identifier of a user account from the client; and based, at least in part, on the received user account identifier, verifying the user account has permission to access the content item namespace. 19. The method of Claim 17, further comprising: receiving an identifier of the content item block server from the client; and wherein the selecting the content item block server to which the content item namespace is assigned is based, at least in part, on the received content item block server identifier from the client. 20. The method of Claim 17, further comprising: storing data representing assignments of content item namespaces to content item block servers; and wherein the selecting the content item block server to which the content item namespace is assigned is based, at least in part, on the data representing the assignments. 21. The method of Claim 17, further comprising: storing data identifying content item blocks stored at the content item block server; and wherein the determining the second set of identifiers of the second content item blocks is based, at least in part, on the data identifying content item blocks stored at the content item block server. 22. The method of Claim 21, further comprising: updating the data identifying content item blocks stored at the content item block server such that the updated data identifying content item blocks stored at the content item block server identifies one or more content item blocks in the first set, that are not in the second set. 23. The method of Claim 17, further comprising: based, at least in part, on the selecting the content item block server to which the content item namespace is assigned, sending 